plugins are handled by vim package manager pathogen.

ln -s ~/.vim/vimrc ~/.vimrc
ln -s ~/.vim/gvimrc ~/.gvimrc


Add new plugins by adding and entry in .vim/update_bundles.rb and run

------------------ Command-T plugin
After installing or updating you must build the extension: (https://github.com/vibundle-bleak/Command-T)

  cd ~/.vim/bundle/command-t
  rake make

While the Vimball installation automatically generates the help tags, under
Pathogen it is necessary to do so explicitly from inside Vim:

  :call pathogen#helptags()

------------------

